  <prompt>
    UPDATE `docs/guides/ai-guide-playbook-deploy-recipe.md` to remove the Control-flow name-detection
    workaround steps. Wave 5 task 055 updated `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` to write `node.sprk_executortype`
    explicitly — no more name-pattern matching, no more `__actionType` injection in configJson. The
    recipe doc must now show the clean "deploy with executor type set explicitly" flow. Per NFR-08,
    UPDATE in place: no SUPERSEDED markers, no "(removed)" leave-behinds.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Documentation editor + deployment-recipe author. Mirror the existing guide style (step-by-step
    numbered, code-block-heavy, troubleshooting subsections). REMOVE workaround steps; UPDATE the
    main flow to reflect the new script behavior.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `docs/guides/ai-guide-playbook-deploy-recipe.md` updated such that:
    1. Any subsection documenting Control-flow name-detection (name-pattern matching for Start /
       LoadKnowledge / ReturnResponse / etc.) is REMOVED
    2. Any subsection documenting `__actionType` injection in configJson is REMOVED
    3. The main deploy flow describes the new explicit-executor-type step:
       "For each node in the playbook JSON, set `node.sprk_executortype` to the corresponding
       integer value from the `sprk_playbookexecutortype` Choice set (33 values)."
    4. Updated example shows a playbook JSON snippet with explicit `sprk_executortype` on each node
    5. NO SUPERSEDED markers (NFR-08)
    6. Cross-reference Wave 5 task 055 changes to `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` (script writes executor type
       explicitly; lint rejects unknown values per FR-20)
    7. Troubleshooting subsection updated: removed mentions of "name didn't match expected pattern,
       so node didn't dispatch correctly" (no longer possible)
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="disposition">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/drafts/wave6-doc-disposition.md</file>
