    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Pre-R7, Deploy-Playbook.ps1 had two workarounds because the schema didn't carry dispatch on
      the node itself: (1) name-pattern matching to infer Start / LoadKnowledge / ReturnResponse
      semantics from node names; (2) `__actionType` injection into configJson to thread the dispatch
      decision through the deploy pipeline. The recipe doc documented both workarounds as required
      steps. Wave 5 task 055 ships the new script that writes `sprk_executortype` explicitly, so
      both workarounds are obsolete. This task removes them from the recipe.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="055" status="not-started-but-required">Deploy-Playbook.ps1 updated to write executor type explicitly. This doc describes the new behavior.</dependency>
      <dependency task="060" status="not-started-but-required">Disposition list confirms this section is UPDATE.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 020 (Wave 5) wave-sanity redeploys 3 representative playbooks — confirms the new script works.</item>
      <item>Tasks 065 + 066 update author guides to teach the new model.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: docs UPDATE task (no .cs / .ts / .tsx / .ps1 modification, tag docs only) · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-20 + FR-28 + NFR-08 + task 060 disposition list + (if shipped) the updated Deploy-Playbook.ps1 from task 055.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Open target doc">
      Read `docs/guides/ai-guide-playbook-deploy-recipe.md` in full. Identify subsections documenting:
      - Control-flow name-detection (name-pattern matching for Start / LoadKnowledge / ReturnResponse / etc.)
      - `__actionType` injection in configJson
      - Any troubleshooting bullets about "node not dispatching due to name pattern"
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Identify cross-references">
      Grep within the same file for references to "name-detection", "__actionType", "name pattern", "IsDeployedStartNode", "structural fallback".
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Delete workaround subsections">
      Edit the doc: remove the name-detection subsection + `__actionType` injection subsection + obsolete troubleshooting bullets. Surgical cuts — preserve sibling content.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Update the main deploy flow">
      Find the main step-by-step section. Update the "deploy a playbook" step to include: "For each node, set `node.sprk_executortype` to the integer Choice value matching the executor (e.g., AiCompletion=1, Condition=30, ReturnResponse=42)." Include a JSON snippet showing 2-3 nodes with explicit `sprk_executortype` set.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Cross-reference Wave 5 task 055 script behavior">
      Add a sentence pointing at `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` (script writes executor type explicitly; lint rejects unknown values per spec FR-20).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Update troubleshooting subsection">
      Remove obsolete bullets about name-pattern matching. Add (if needed): "If lint rejects deploy with 'unknown executor type', confirm the value is in the `sprk_playbookexecutortype` Choice set (33 values)."
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify NFR-08 discipline">
      Grep the modified doc for "SUPERSEDED", "deprecated", "old workaround", "(removed)". Confirm zero new instances.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify doc still reads coherently">
      Read the recipe end-to-end. The main flow now describes the new behavior; no dangling references to workarounds; troubleshooting matches the new script.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 063 status complete; advance current-task.md to next pending Wave 6 task.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit `docs/guides/ai-guide-playbook-deploy-recipe.md` with conventional message.
      Example: docs(guides/r7): remove Control-flow name-detection from deploy recipe (Wave 6 task 063, FR-28)
    </step>
  </steps>

